  "prompt": "How do I log in my Facebook account if you forgot your password?",
  "response": "If you\u2019ve forgotten your Facebook password, you can reset it by following these steps:\n\n1. **Go to the Facebook login page.** Open your web browser and go to [www.facebook.com](https://www.facebook.com).\n\n2. **Click on \"Forgotten password?\"** This link is located under the password field.\n\n3. **Enter your email or phone number.** On the next page, enter the email address or phone number linked to your account and click \"Search.\"\n\n4. **Choose your recovery option.** Facebook will show you a list of options for receiving a code to reset your password, such as via email or SMS. Choose the method that works best for you and click \"Continue.\"\n\n5. **Check your email or SMS.** If you chose to receive a code via email, check your inbox (and the spam/junk folder) for an email from Facebook. If you opted for a text message, check your messages for a text from Facebook.\n\n6. **Enter the code.** Once you receive the code, enter it in the provided field on the Facebook page and click \"Continue.\"\n\n7. **Create a new password.** Follow the prompts to enter a new password. Make sure it\u2019s strong and unique. \n\n8. **Log in with your new password.** After you've successfully reset your password, you can log in with your new credentials.\n\nIf you encounter any issues during this process, you can visit Facebook\u2019s Help Center for additional assistance.",
